    "This leads to a legislative vacuum where the major industry players would have to settle upon the rules themselves.",
    "Delegating the authority of AI regulation to the business world is a radical yet intriguing proposition.",
    "The approach could leverage the agility, innovation, and deep technical expertise that businesses possess.",
    "Companies at the forefront of AI development have an intimate understanding of the technology's nuances and are well-positioned to anticipate and manage the risks associated with AI.",
    "By delegating regulatory or normative authority to these businesses, regulations could evolve in tandem with the technology, ensuring more timely and relevant oversight."
